n, set in train countless research projects, is difficult to document and has not been assessed until now. This volume, using the testimonies of key witnesses and participants in the semiotic project, offers a picture of how Sebeok, through his development of knowledge of endosemiotics, phytosemiotics, biosemiotics and sociosemiotics, enabled semiotics in general to redraw the boundaries of science and the humanities as well as nature and culture.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aSemiotics. 4aKommunikation. 4aSemiotik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCommunication.  aSemiotics.1 aAnderson, Myrdene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBehar, Lisa Block de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrier, Søren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobley, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobley, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCunningham, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanesi, Marcel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeely, Brooke Williams, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeely, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeely, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGorlée, Dinda L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoffmeyer, Jesper, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohansen, Jørgen Dines, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKull, Kalevi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKull, Kal